.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-bundle 1  "rom-weaver-bundle "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-bundle \- Create and parse rom\-weaver\-bundle.json workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver bundle\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create and parse rom\-weaver\-bundle.json workflows
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
rom\-weaver\-bundle\-create(1)
Build, validate, and write a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle from local ROM/patch files
.TP
rom\-weaver\-bundle\-parse(1)
Parse and validate a rom\-weaver\-bundle.json bundle (plain, stream\-codec compressed, or inside an archive) and resolve its ROM/patch entries
